e's ''Last Week I Asked You'' series.\n| align=\"center\" | <ref group =\"\u2021\" name=\"LWIAY00107\">{{cite AV media|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Old1YzSG_S8|title=I went on a break for 30 days & THIS HAPPENED - LWIAY #00107 |date=21 February 2020 |publisher=[[YouTube]] |access-date=30 March 2020 |work=[[PewDiePie]]}}</ref>\n| align=\"center\" | <ref name=\"Katzowitz2020\">{{cite web|last=Katzowitz|first=Josh|url=https://www.dailydot.com/upstream/pewdiepie-returns-to-youtube/|title=PewDiePie returns to YouTube after 37-day hiatus|work=[[The Daily Dot]]|date=21 February 2020|access-date=30 March 2020}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==Collaborative videography==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+Key\n|-\n| align=\"center\" style=\"background:#B2BEB5;\"| ^\n| Denotes videos that have now been unlisted on YouTube.\n|-\n| align=\"center\" style=\"background:#9090C0;\"| \u00b6\n| Denotes videos that have now been made private on YouTube.\n|-\n| style=\"background:#AA98A9;\"| {{\u2020}}\n| Denotes videos that have now been removed from YouTube.\n|}\n\n<!-- Due to the sheer volume of PewDiePie's YouTube videography, this listing is meant to only include videos embedded in articles by media outlets. If only a hyperlink to the video is made available by the media outlet, only include it within this list if the outlet includes an accompanying description of the video (i.e. not just hyperlink in passing).-->\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+PewDiePie's collaborative appearances on other YouTube channels<br/>(listed by upload date)\n! style=\"width:20em;\"| Video name\n! style=\"width:8em;\" align=\"center\" data-sort-type=date | Channel\n! style=\"width:8em;\" align=\"center\" data-sort-type=date | Upload date\n! style=\"width:45em;\" class=\"unsortable\" | Description / notes\n! style=\"width:2em;\" class=\"unsortable\" | Video\n! style=\"width:2em;\" class=\"unsortable\" | {{tooltip|Ref.|Reference(s)}}\n|-\n| \"Rasputin vs Stalin. Epic Rap Battles of History\"\n| align=\"center\" | [[Epi